        <h1 class="heading-1">1. GENERAL INFORMATION</h1>
        <div>
          <p>
            As of the insurance Contract In Force Date, we agree to cover the
            Insured from against certain risks under the quaranteed coverage you
            have selected. Specific provisions apply to each coverage to explain
            their particularities
          </p>
          <p>
            In exchange, you agree that the Premiums will be paid. The Premiums
            must be paid on the date they are due A period of forty-five (45)
            days is allowed for the Premium to be paid. This period is called
            the Grace Period
          </p>
          <p>At the end of this period, your Contract:</p>
          <ul class="bulleted">
            <li>
              is cancelled for non-payment of Premium, i.e. it terminates; or
            </li>
            <li>
              is maintained in force under the specific provisions applicable to
              the coverages.
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            If your Contract terminates for non-payment of Premium, you can
            request the reinstatement of your Contract within two (2) years
            following the date of cancellation for non-payment of Premium.
          </p>
          <p>
            When a risk for which an Insured is covered occurs, we agree to pay
            you Pragnesh the Beneficiary the insurance amount shown in the
            policy summary or any other amount as per the specific provisions
            applicable to a coverage.
          </p>
          <p>
            If you terminate your Contract within ten (10) days following its In
            Force Date, we will refund the first paid Premium.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

